<div class="content">
  <p>
    Pushing to the stack is simply a matter of linking to a route that is a
    subroute so that the toolbar is rendered with a back button (defined in
    <code>stack-navigation.hbs</code> on the previous page).
  </p>

  <p>
    For example we could link to <code>stack1</code> with the
    <code>\{{link-to}}</code> helper:
  </p>

{{#code-highlight lang="handlebars"}}
\{{#link-to "stack-navigation.stack1"}}
  Push to stack
\{{/link-to}}
{{/code-highlight}}

  <p>
    To pop from the stack we assigned the <code>goBack</code> action to the
    <code>\{{ons-back-button}}</code>:
  </p>

{{#code-highlight lang="handlebars"}}
\{{ons-back-button click=(action "goBack")}}
{{/code-highlight}}

  <p>And in our <code>stack-navigation</code> controller define the actions as:</p>

{{#code-highlight lang="js"}}
// controllers/stack-navigation.js
actions: {
  goBack() {
    window.history.back();
  }
}
{{/code-highlight}}

  <p style="text-align: center">
    {{#link-to "stack-navigation.stack3" tagName="ons-button"}}
      Learn about animations with liquid-fire
    {{/link-to}}
  </p>
</div>
